Remarks. The specimens herein examined match the original description, except for the length of the proventricle, which is longer in Brazilian specimens (3.5–5 chaetigers, as opposed to 2–3 chaetigers, as in the original description). In addition, although not mentioned in the text of the original description, Benham illustrated a specimen with dorsal cirri on chaetiger 2 (
Benham 1921: Pl. 5, Fig. 11
), while in Brazilian specimens, dorsal cirri are absent on chaetiger 2. Both these differences, however, could not be confirmed in the specimens examined from other localities, including the syntypes , all specimens being remarkably similar to the Brazilian ones.
